headline.main: JAPANESE CLAIM 5 ALLIED WARSHIPS; Tokyo Says Planes Sank Two Battleships, 3 Cruisers in the Solomons -- OWI Skeptical BLOWS TRADED IN THE SOUTHWEST PACIFIC JAPANESE CLAIM 5 ALLIED WARSHIPS

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Feb. 1 -- The Tokyo radio quoted Admiral Shigetaro Shimada, Navy Minister, as telling the Diet today that Japanese planes sank two battleships and three cruisers off the most southerly point of the Solomons last Friday and Saturday.
abstract: Japanese claim Jap plans sank 2 battleships, 3 cruisers, and damaged battleship and cruiser off Rennell Is; map
